snippet: The latest cache of documents in the Florida killing focuses on the character of the defendant, George Zimmerman.
abstract: Wide-ranging FBI assessment of George Zimmerman finds that the accused murderer was not prone to violence or prejudice and moved easily between racial and ethnic groups; assessment is part of a pretrial cache of documents in the case that have been released periodically by special prosecutor Angela B Corey.

byline.contributor: Serge F. Kovaleski contributed reporting from New York.

lead_paragraph: The latest cache of documents in the Florida killing focuses on the character of the defendant, George Zimmerman.

headline.seo: More Records Released in Trayvon Martin Case
